headline: Trump Sues IRS, Treasury for $10 Billion for Tax-Return Leak
summary: The suit was filed Thursday in Miami federal court by Trump, his sons Donald Jr. and Eric, and the Trump Organization, which manages the president’s real estate holdings.  Trump had long criticized the IRS for allegedly working to undermine him for political purposes.  Trump’s lawsuit revisits a clash that took center stage weeks before the 2020 election, when the New York Times published an explosive report on Trump’s tax records that was based on leaked IRS data.

headline: American Express Falls After Earnings. The Stock Is Having a Rocky Start to 2026.
summary: Shares of  American Express  dropped Friday after the credit-card giant’s quarterly earnings slightly missed analysts’ estimates and its 2026 outlook met expectations.  American Express stock fell 2.7% Friday.  President Donald Trump’s call to cap credit-card interest rates at 10% for one year hasn’t helped, though that policy may have a more muted impact on American Express’ generally high-credit clientele.
